rows.title: Chainsaw Man
rows.titleText: You are In a world where Devils are born from humanityâ€™s deepest fears, survival is a brutal struggle. The more humans dread something the Devils, the stronger its Devil becomes. To fight back, governments and underground organizations employ Devil Hunters, humans who make contracts with Devils, trading pieces of their bodies or souls for power.

objects.title: Character-Insert
objects.text: You replace the character that already existed in the Chainsaw Man world, when you get inserted you will keep their power and memories.

objects.title: Reincarnation
objects.text: You will reincarnate as someone you made with your criteria, and you will gain their memories. You shall have all their memories and skills, you'll be able to act just like they did. You can decide how far you merge, if it's just your mind in their body with their memories and skills, or if your personalities merge completely.

objects.title: Drop-in
objects.text: You right now will be dropped in this world with no identity, no history, and nothing but your clothes right now,

objects.title: Original Character
objects.text: You reincarnate into an original character, you can choose their appearance, age, and occupation freely.

objects.title: Twin
objects.text: You become the twin of an existing character.

objects.title: Sibling
objects.text: You are a sibling of an existing character.

objects.title: Family Member
objects.text: You are a member of the family (cousin, and so on) of an existing character.

rows.title: Age
rows.titleText: The age you will take over or merge with the body.

objects.title: Human
objects.text: In the world of Chainsaw Man, humans live in constant fear of Devils born from their deepest fears. Some make contracts with Devils for power, but most are just prey trying to survive another day. But don't underestimate them, for they are the many.

objects.title: Hybrid
objects.text: Hybrids are humans fused with Devil powers, granting them immense strength and regeneration at the cost of their humanity. Theyâ€™re neither fully human nor Devilâ€”just weapons trapped in an endless cycle of violence. How you get it is on you, from a surgery or a contract, or any other means.

objects.title: Fiend
objects.text: Fiends are Devils who have taken over human corpses, blending monstrous power with a twisted imitation of humanity. Though they retain some of their host's appearance and traits, their hunger towards humans is still there, waiting.

objects.title: Devil
objects.text: Devils are monstrous incarnations of humanity's deepest fearsâ€”the more a concept is dreaded, the stronger the Devil becomes. They thrive on chaos and suffering, offering cursed power to desperate humans in exchange for gruesome prices. If the human that you have a contract with dies, the power you gave to them will come back to you.

objects.title: Average

objects.title: Scarred
objects.text: You are scarred. You would look average if not for your scars and are not prone to getting acne.

objects.title: Ugly
objects.text: You are ugly and somewhat unattractive. And prone to getting acne.

objects.title: Hideous
objects.text: You are hideous. You are the definition of what ugly is, but threaten not you are still you in your hearth King.

rows.title: Identity
rows.titleText:
You've chosen to character-insert into someone you know of from the Chainsaw Man World. Who will it be?

Alternatively, if you chose Reincarnation as your Incarnation method this is the section where if you're reincarnated as a twin, sibling or family member you pick which character you are related to.

addons.title: Human Indomitable Spirit
addons.text: Your unbreakable will and refusal to surrender allow you to thrive in a world that rejects you. When facing impossible odds, like fighting a high-end devil with only your fists and a rock, you become just temporarily slightly stronger. Victory isnâ€™t guaranteed, but the impossible becomes almost impossible. This applies beyond battle: in life-or-death moments, you think faster, react sharper, and even learn faster. The more hopeless or outclassed you are, the more your will pushes your body farther.

objects.title: Invictus
objects.text: Your will is unbreakableâ€”unbound and unending. Your body may bend or break, but your will never will. This doesnâ€™t mean you wonâ€™t feel emotions; youâ€™ll experience them as deeply as anyone. The difference is, your heart and mind will never yield. Example The Falling Devil's powerâ€”the one that makes minds collapse into despairâ€”won't work on you. At all. You will thriveâ€”but remember, your body can still be broken.

addons.title: Weapon Hybrid
addons.text: As a hybrid, you instinctively master your body and abilities from the start. You know your exact limits - every ounce of strength, every drop of power. You are a living weapon. A perfect hybrid. A natural killing machine. This applies to all hybrids - Weapon, Nail, Needle - every last one of you is born battle-ready.

objects.title: Battle Instinct
objects.text: This isnâ€™t skillâ€”itâ€™s instinct. Unlike others, your lizard brain already knows how to fight: how to dodge, strike, and move for maximum damageâ€”even untrained. But with formal training? Your potential explodes. In this world, thatâ€™s what it takes to survive, and your instinct knows that. (In skills, Combat Capabilities are discounted)

addons.title: Immortal
addons.text: As a Fiend, you're now immortal like Hybrids - with the same insane regeneration. Chopped to pieces? You won't die. Pour blood into your remains and you'll rebuild yourself limb by limb. Only complete destruction can kill you for good. Blood is fuel. Earth is full.

objects.title: Regenerator
objects.text: Your healing factor has upgraded. Human injuries that should take weeks vanish in days. For Hybrids, Fiends, and Devils? Your blood goes twice as farâ€”regenerate the same damage for half the cost of blood. Efficiency is survival.

addons.title: Devil Amplified
addons.text: You are the King of Terror. As a Devil, you already grow stronger from human fearâ€”but now you break all limits. The dread of Devils, the panic of animalsâ€”it all fuels you. And this also make human fear power you more than usual.

objects.title: Fear Amplified
objects.text: You wield fear like a weapon. Devils second-guess their decision of challenging you. Hybrids lose the will to fight. Humans surrender to despair. Whatever the species, you know exactly how to break themâ€”and even creatures that donâ€™t know fear... will learn it from you.

objects.title: Plot Armor
objects.text: Plot armor protects you. Stray bullets, falling debrisâ€”mundane accidents won't kill you. The only way you die is if someone wants you dead and actively tries to make it happen.

objects.title: Manton Protected
objects.text: You have Manton Protectionâ€”immune to certain 'bullshit' instant-kill abilities. Example the Water Devil can't liquefy your brain or crush your heart just because it controls water. But a boulder hurled at your face? That'll still kill you if you can't dodge or tank it

objects.title: Body+
objects.text: You exceed your species' limits. As a human, you rival Olympic athletes or even surpass them. As a Fiend, you toss cars. Strength, speed, durabilityâ€”all pushed beyond normal bounds of your species.

objects.title: Ladies Luck
objects.text: The universe bends to your will. Luck isn't just on your sideâ€”it fights for you. Success comes easier. Failure retreats. This won't make you win the lottery, but in battle? In survival? Every dice roll matters.

addons.title: The Real Deal
addons.text: All style. Now? Style with skill. The more badass you act in combat, the sharper, stronger, and faster you becomeâ€”temporarily. In the zone? Every move isnâ€™t just coolâ€”itâ€™s lethal. But slip up? Back to just looking good.

objects.title: Badass
objects.text: This isn't about powerâ€”it's about style. You don't fight better or hit harder. You just make everything look badass. Walking? Badass. Breathing? Badass. Every damn thing you do oozes cool. No substance, all swagger.

objects.title: Makimaâ€™s Echo
objects.text: Words are your weapon. You master of human words flip a madman into calm, twist an innocent into violence, force beliefs into hollow minds. Knives cut flesh, but your words gut souls.

objects.title: Devils Child
objects.text: Devils value you beyond reason. In contracts, they offer more than you giveâ€”your nail is worth three human lives; a drop of your blood is the same worth for another's sight. This isn't affectionâ€”it's your sheer worth. And it scales depending on your status or how much the devil you're contracting with like youâ€”your 'normal' self is worth less than a country's president, but your 'president' self? Worth more than every world leader combined.

objects.title: Hell Tourist
objects.text: You can rip open doors to Hellâ€”anywhere, anytime. And on the side note, you step into Hell in Tokyo, crawl out in New York. It's fast travel like Minecraft's Nether... just with more bad time and things that want to wear your skin.

objects.title: Empathy
objects.text: Empathy is your weaponâ€”forged not from kindness, but precision. You donâ€™t just see hidden emotionsâ€”you feel them: grief behind grins, rage beneath courtesy, even the sick joy in anotherâ€™s pain. Most ignore these cracks. You? You pry them open. A trembling hand, a strained laughâ€”all become levers to twist souls. Devils arenâ€™t immune, either. Their hunger, their hesitationâ€”it all screams to you, with it, you will know their weakness. In this world, understanding is the sharpest blade. You cannot solve a problem if you don't know the cause of the problem, even Logic knows that.

objects.title: Cannibal
objects.text: As a Hybrid, you can now steal any Hybrid's or in special cases Devil's hybrid formâ€”even custom ones and have never seen before in the manga/anime. The catch? You must devour at least half their body weight. The new form starts with weakened versions of their powers, gradually reaching full strength. But Battle Instinct and Weapon Hybrid perks remain locked on the new form until the form is fully matured.

objects.title: Devil Form+
objects.text: As a Fiend, you can now awaken your true Devil Formâ€”an upgraded, more powerful version of your original Devil form. The catch? It burns through blood at a rapid rate. (With the Regenerator perk, the total cost of blood is halved, but the speed of consumption remains) Push too hard, and you'll bleed yourself dry before the fight's over, but push enough you will decimate them.

objects.title: Contract Devil
objects.text: You understand contractsâ€”and how to weaponize them. While other Devils trade for fear or amusement, you deal in pure power. Every pact secretly converts the recipient's offering into strengthâ€”just like fear fuels Devils. And if they die? You reclaim the power you lent... but keep their original payment. A single soul offers little, but a city's worth? A nation's? That could make you rival the Primal Fears themselves."

objects.title: Valueless
objects.text: Devil just don't find any value in you to give you contracts.

objects.title: Chainsaw Hearth
objects.text: Devils and humans hunt your heartâ€”just like Denji. No one knows why... except the Devil inside you. So ready your weapons. The suffering starts now.

objects.title: Rot
objects.text: Your host body is rotting, you need fresh blood to keep you from rotting apart.

objects.title: Devils Hatred
objects.text: Youâ€™re a true Devil now. What does that mean? Simple: Everyone hates youâ€” even other Devils. This makes it harder for you to find a Human that is willing to make a contract with you.

objects.title: Kobeniâ€™s Luck
objects.text: You are unlucky. This doesn't mean you are powerless you can circumvent much of the bad luck with wits, it would just be painful.

objects.title: Weak Body
objects.text: Your physical traits are bottom-tier for your species. If you're human, you gain strength at half the normal rate and catch your sickness easily.

objects.title: Gun Devilâ€™s List
objects.text: You're in Gun Devil hit list. (This stacks with Chainsaw Hearth)

objects.title: Narcissism
objects.text: Your egoâ€™s swollen beyond reasonâ€”now your only obsession is staying flawless 24/7. Combat? Survival? Secondary. The real battle is keeping your hair perfect in the middle of a bloodbath. And you canâ€™t stand even the thought of someone being better than you. If they are, youâ€™ll drag them down below you, no matter the cost, Allies or not.

objects.title: Battle Junkie
objects.text: Youâ€™re a Battle Junkieâ€”addicted to the raw thrill of combat. Victory, challenge, destructionâ€”you crave it all. The rush of violence hits like hard drugs, twisting your mind. You want to pick a fight with anyone, and if you don't act upon it, your mood will go down, making you more prone to anger.

objects.title: Inhumanity
objects.text: Youâ€™ve lost touch with your humanity. You see others as separate, lesserâ€”maybe even as pets or toys. Whether you feel superior, protective, or just indifferent, you canâ€™t relate to them. You donâ€™t understand them. They donâ€™t understand you.

objects.title: Berserk
objects.text: When you feel true rage, you become slightly powerful, but the true rage takes over, you don't just kill the bully tormenting your sonâ€”you crush your own child's skull in the same frenzied swing. When a Devil bites your best friend's head off in battle, your vengeance leaves both the monster and your surviving allies in bloody pieces. That's the curse of your berserk fury: it always destroys the very things you're trying to protect, leaving you standing in a circle of corpses you made with your own hands.

objects.title: Devil in Human Skin
objects.text: You think you love food, sex, or romance? No. What you truly love is killingâ€”feeling life drain from your victims, watching their existence bleed away. It gives you pleasure, purpose in this twisted world. And if you donâ€™t kill? You sufferâ€”agonizing withdrawal, worse than any drug. This doesnâ€™t mean you canâ€™t feel love or empathy. You might even cherish your loved onesâ€¦ enough to save them for last.

rows.title: Drawbacks
rows.titleText: Thereâ€™s a way to counter these drawbacks, but youâ€™ll need to figure it out on your own, maybe a contract, perhaps?

objects.title: Fox Front Paw
objects.text:
You can summon the Fox Devil's paws to swipe or crush anything in sight.

Each summon costs a piece of your armsâ€”skin, flesh, bone, nails, or nerves. The Fox Devil takes its payment immediately.

objects.title: Fox Back Legs
objects.text:
You can summon the Fox Devil's Legs to kick or crush anything in sight.

Each summon costs a piece of your legsâ€”skin, flesh, bone, nails, or nerves. The Fox Devil takes its payment immediately..

objects.title: Fox Head
objects.text:
You can summon the Fox Devil's head to bite or devour targets.

In exchange, each attack costs a body part of your choice.

objects.title: Fox Devil
objects.text:
Whether through good relationship or being its favored contractorâ€”regardless of the reasonâ€”the Fox Devil has granted you the power to summon its full Devil form in combat.

In exchange, every total 10 seconds the Fox Devil is summoned, it devours a piece of you. But bewareâ€”prolong the fight too long, and you may run out of you to feed it.

objects.title: Future's Eye
objects.text:
You can see flashes of the futureâ€”an incredibly powerful ability, if your mind and body can keep up. 

The price? You're guaranteed to suffer the worst fucking death. No clue when, where, or how... but it's coming for you.

objects.title: Future's Dream
objects.text:
Your Future Devil contract lets you dream of tomorrowâ€™s events with 85% accuracy. The details may shiftâ€”when or where something happensâ€”but the core truth remains. Dream of a Devil attacking at dinner? It might strike at lunch instead, but youâ€™ll recognize it and grasp its abilities. Not perfect, but enough to never be caught off guard. Remember, Information is power.

In exchange, the Future Devil permanently steals your natural ability to dream and takes memories equal to your vision's duration (5-hour prophecy = 5 hours of erased memories). The stolen memories are selected at random - it might be forgotten meals or your mother's face. Even video evidence feels alien; watching recordings of your forgotten self is like observing a stranger puppeteering your body... if that even was you to begin with.

objects.title: Beginner
objects.text: Your combat skills are entry-levelâ€”straight out of a Devil Hunter Club handbook. Textbook basics, zero real experience. You will have a hard time taking out a lower tier devil, but with a group you will be fine.

objects.title: Competent
objects.text: Your combat skills are Public Safety standardâ€”enough to scrap with low-tier Devils solo, but against a medium-tier? Even with a squad, it's a hard fought.

objects.title: Combat Expert
objects.text: Your combat skills are Kishibe-trainedâ€”brutal, efficient, and just sharp enough to gut a medium-tier Devil with effort. But a high-tier Devil? Pray itâ€™s feeling merciful.

defaultRowText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.
defaultChoiceText: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.
